  <body> <button id="theme-toggle" title="Toggle dark mode"> Dark Mode</button>
    <h4>Are you comfortable talking ?</h4>
    <p></p>
    <div class="ent General">
      <h3>1ST COMPLAINT: PAIN IN THE THROAT (Sore Throat)</h3>
      <!-- S: Site -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Site</span>
        <span class="verbal">"Can you point to where the pain is worst? Is it on
          one side or all over?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>GENERALIZED / CENTRAL:&nbsp;<span class="infectious"></span></li>
          <ul>
            <li><span class="infectious">Viral Pharyngitis</span></li>
            <li><span class="infectious">Bacterial Tonsillitis</span></li>
          </ul>
          <li>UNILATERAL (one-sided): </li>
          <ul>
            <li><b class="ent infectious emergency">Peritonsillar Abscess
                (Quinsy)</b></li>
          </ul>
          <li>RETROSTERNAL / BURNING: </li>
          <ul>
            <li class="git"><span>GERD /GORD)</span></li>
          </ul>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- O: Onset -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>O</strong>: Onset</span>
        <span class="verbal">"When did the sore throat start? Did it come on
          suddenly?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>ACUTE (&lt; 2 weeks):&nbsp;<span class="infectious"></span></li>
          <ul>
            <li><span class="infectious">Viral <br>
              </span></li>
            <li><span class="infectious">Bacterial Infection</span></li>
          </ul>
          <li>CHRONIC (&gt; 3 weeks): </li>
          <ul>
            <li><b class="oncology ent">Red flag - consider malignancy</b>,&nbsp;<span
                class="git"></span></li>
            <li><span class="git">GORD</span>,&nbsp;<span class="ent"></span></li>
            <li><span class="ent">Chronic tonsillitis</span></li>
          </ul>
          <li>Triggered by sick contacts?</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- D: Duration -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>D</strong>: Duration</span>
        <span class="verbal">"How many days have you had this for?"</span> </li>
      <!-- A/R: Aggravating / Relieving Factors -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>A/R</strong>:
          Aggravating &amp; Relieving Factors</span> <span class="verbal">"Does
          anything make the pain better or worse?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>AGGRAVATING: </li>
          <ul>
            <li>Swallowing (Odynophagia), </li>
            <li>talking, </li>
            <li>eating</li>
          </ul>
          <li>RELIEVING: </li>
          <ul>
            <li>Simple analgesia (paracetamol, ibuprofen), </li>
            <li>warm drinks</li>
          </ul>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- C: Character -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>C</strong>:
          Character</span> <span class="verbal">"What does the pain feel like?
          Is it scratchy, sharp like swallowing glass, or more like a lump?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>SCRATCHY / RAW: <span class="infectious">Typical for viral
              pharyngitis</span></li>
          <li>SEVERE / SHARP: <span class="infectious">Suggests bacterial
              tonsillitis or quinsy</span></li>
          <li>BURNING: <span class="git">Suggests GORD</span></li>
          <li>"LUMP" SENSATION: <span class="General">Globus pharyngeus</span>,
            <b class="oncology">or a mass</b></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- R: Radiation -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>:
          Radiation</span> <span class="verbal">"Does the pain travel anywhere,
          for example, to your ears?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="ent">Referred otalgia (ear pain) is common in severe
            tonsillitis/pharyngitis</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- A: Associated Symptoms (THE KEY DIFFERENTIATOR) -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>A</strong>:
          Associated Symptoms</span> <span class="verbal">"Along with the sore
          throat, have you had a fever, cough, runny nose, or any difficulty
          opening your mouth?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>hoarseness</li>
          <li><b>CLUES FOR BACTERIAL (Strep Throat - Centor/ Fever PAIN
              criteria):</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="infectious">Fever</li>
              <li class="infectious ent">Tonsillar exudates (pus on tonsils)</li>
              <li class="infectious ent">Tender anterior cervical lymph nodes</li>
              <li class="infectious respiratory"><b>Absence</b> of cough</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li><b>CLUES FOR VIRAL:</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="infectious respiratory">Cough, coryza (runny nose),
                sneezing -&gt; <b><u>Common </u><u>Cold</u></b></li>
              <li class="infectious">Profound fatigue, widespread <b><u>lymph </u><u>nodes
                    </u></b>-&gt; Infectious Mononucleosis (Glandular Fever)</li>
              <li class="infectious ent"><b><u>Hoarseness </u></b>-&gt; <b><u>Laryngitis</u></b></li>
              <li class="infectious ent"><b><u><br>
                  </u></b></li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li><b>CLUES FOR DEEP INFECTION (Quinsy):</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="ent emergency">Muffled "hot potato" voice</li>
              <li class="ent emergency"><b><u>Trismus </u></b>(difficulty
                opening the jaw)</li>
              <li class="ent emergency"><b><u>Drooling </u></b>/ inability to
                swallow saliva</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li><b>CLUES FOR GORD:</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="git">Heartburn, regurgitation, symptoms worse when
                lying down or after meals</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>SUBACUTE THYROIDITIS</p>
          </li>
          <ul>
            <li>ass with viral infections.....</li>
          </ul>
          <li>Lumps and bumps anywhere</li>
          <ul>
            <li>abdominal fullness</li>
          </ul>
          <li>
            <ul>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- P: Progression -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>:
          Progression</span> <span class="verbal">"Since it started, has it
          been getting progressively worse?"</span> </li>
      <!-- P: Pattern -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>: Pattern</span>
        <span class="verbal">"Is the pain constant or intermittent?"</span> </li>
      <!-- E: Effect on life -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>E</strong>: Effect
          on Life</span> <span class="verbal">"How has this affected you? Are
          you able to eat and drink normally?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>Assess for risk of dehydration if odynophagia is severe</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- R: Red Flags -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>: Red
          Flags</span> <span class="verbal">"I need to ask some specific
          questions to make sure we're not missing anything serious."</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="ent respiratory emergency"><b>patches </b>/ <b>clour
              change</b></li>
          <li class="ent respiratory emergency">Diptheria</li>
          <li class="ent respiratory emergency">candidiasis</li>
          <li class="ent respiratory emergency">voice changes/ nodes</li>
          <ul>
            <li class="ent respiratory emergency">quinsy</li>
            <li class="ent respiratory emergency">laryngeal cancer</li>
          </ul>
          <li class="ent respiratory emergency"><b>AIRWAY COMPROMISE:</b> </li>
          <ul>
            <li class="ent respiratory emergency">Stridor (noisy breathing), </li>
            <li class="ent respiratory emergency">difficulty breathing, </li>
            <li class="ent respiratory emergency">drooling</li>
          </ul>
          <li class="ent infectious emergency"><b>DEEP NECK SPACE INFECTION:</b>
          </li>
          <ul>
            <li class="ent infectious emergency">Muffled voice,</li>
            <li class="ent infectious emergency">&nbsp;trismus, </li>
            <li class="ent infectious emergency">severe unilateral swelling, </li>
            <li class="ent infectious emergency">neck stiffness</li>
          </ul>
          <li class="oncology ent"><b>SUSPECTED MALIGNANCY:</b> </li>
          <ul>
            <li class="oncology ent">Sore throat &gt; 3 weeks, </li>
            <li class="oncology ent">persistent <em>hoarseness</em>, </li>
            <li class="oncology ent">weight loss, </li>
            <li class="oncology ent">neck lump</li>
          </ul>
          <li class="infectious hematology">Systemic illness: </li>
          <ul>
            <li class="infectious hematology">Non-blanching rash, </li>
            <li class="infectious hematology">signs of sepsis</li>
          </ul>
          <li class="infectious">Inability to <em>swallow </em>fluids (risk of
            dehydration)</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- S: Scale -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Severity
          / Scale</span> <span class="verbal">"On a scale of 1 to 10, how would
          you rate the pain?"</span> </li>
    </div>
